A/6, V/8

Image is slightly tilted down to the left throughout most of the film and, like it says, the subs are present throughout. There's some mild contrast issues here and there, dark scenes are pretty damn dark.

Audio is fairly clear, but there are still audience reactions present (though I have to say the reactions are mild to what they were in the theater I went to).

All in all, this copy is very watchable, audio is only slightly tinny and everyone can be heard well.
Also, it does NOT contain the clip at the end (as you can see our brave cameraman quickly hiding the camera as the credits begin).
